# Migrate X — Project Structure

This is a monorepo with two top-level packages:

```
backend/   — Dart HTTP server (shelf + shelf_router)
frontend/  — Flutter app (Material 3 + Riverpod)
```

## Architecture Rules

- Backend architecture is flat and modular. No deeply nested folders, no abstract repository layers, no DI frameworks.
- Backend has exactly these top-level lib files: `config.dart`, `cors.dart`, `logger.dart`, `exceptions.dart` and two subdirectories: `services/`, `routes/`.
- Frontend uses Riverpod for all state management. No `setState` except trivial local UI.
- Frontend is a single-page pipeline app. All UI lives in `lib/screens/home/` with the `PipelineNotifier` managing the upload-to-download flow.
- Shared providers live in `lib/providers/`, shared widgets in `lib/widgets/`, models in `lib/models/`.
- Every Riverpod provider lives in its own file.
- No code generation unless explicitly approved (riverpod_annotation codegen is allowed).
- All files use `lowercase_with_underscores`. All classes use `UpperCamelCase`.
- TODO comments mark future LLM integration points. Do not remove them.

## Adding New Features

- New backend endpoints: add a route file in `backend/lib/routes/`, mount it in `bin/server.dart`.
- New backend logic: add a service file in `backend/lib/services/`, inject it into routes.
- New frontend pipeline sections: add widgets in `frontend/lib/screens/home/`, extend `PipelineStage` and `PipelineNotifier` as needed.
- New shared state: add a provider file in `frontend/lib/providers/`.
- New shared UI components: add in `frontend/lib/widgets/`.
- New data classes: add in `frontend/lib/models/` with a `fromJson` factory.
